Opening (10 seconds)
“AI is dramatically accelerating software development. Tools like Copilot, Claude Code and Devin can generate huge amounts of code.

But none of them answer a simple enterprise question:

Why does this code exist?”


Point to Monitor 1 — The Why

“Software delivery has evolved through several paradigms.

Waterfall gave us planning but no adaptability.
Agile gave us speed but fragmented context.
DevOps gave us automation but not understanding.
And now AI tools are generating code faster than ever.

To explain this evolution, we use a Jurassic World analogy.

In every era, a dominant species believed it had mastered survival.
The Brachiosaurus was powerful but slow to change.
The Gallimimus was fast but ran in circles.
The Spinosaurus was strong but destructive.
And the Indominus was engineered for speed but impossible to govern.

Every species believed it had solved evolution.

But the one that actually survived was different.

It was smart enough to collaborate.

Across all these SDLC eras, the same thing keeps happening:

Intent gets lost.

Business decisions live in Jira.
Architecture lives in documents.
Code lives in Git.
Test evidence lives somewhere else.

No system connects them.

That’s the coherence gap.”



Move to Monitor 2 — The How

“This is where Smart SDLC comes in.

Smart SDLC builds a delivery graph that connects:

business intent → architecture decisions → stories → code → tests → deployments → evidence.

And it exposes that through role-aware workspaces.”


Point to Demo Roles

“For example:

A Product Owner sees AI-validated stories and impact analysis.

A Developer sees intent, ADRs and constraints directly inside the IDE while coding.

A Director sees real-time delivery confidence without status meetings.

Everyone is looking at the same connected delivery graph.”

Closing (10 seconds)

“So instead of searching across tools, you can ask:

Why does this logic exist?

And the system shows the entire lineage instantly.

AI helped us build software faster.

Smart SDLC helps us build the right thing — coherently and traceably at enterprise scale.”
